HEADWORD: face-saving
<hw>face-saving</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>allowing one to
maintain one's dignity or prestige; designed to avoid admitting
something embarrassing; <as>as, a <ex>face-saving</ex> compromise</as>;
-- of actions.</def>⟦br⟧
